    is_real_schur as Boolean
    eigenvalues as NDArray.NDArray
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: LU Decomposition with partial pivoting
Process called "lu_decompose" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and pivot as Optional[PivotStrategy] returns LUDecomposition:
    Let strategy be pivot or PartialPivoting
    Let n be A.shape at index 0
    Let m be A.shape at index 1
    Let k be Math.min with a as n and b as m Let L be NDArray.eye with size as n
    Let U be NDArray.copy_array with arr as A
    Let P be NDArray.eye with size as n
    Let perm_count be 0 For col from 0 to k - 1:
    Note: Find pivot
    Let pivot_row be col
    If strategy is PartialPivoting:
    Let max_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as U.data at index (col multiplied by m col)
    For row from col 1 to n - 1:
    Let val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as U.data at index (row multiplied by m col)
    If val is greater than max_val:
    Set max_val to val
    Set pivot_row to row Note: Swap rows if needed
    If pivot_row is not equal to col:
    swap_matrix_rows with matrix as U and row1 as col and row2 as pivot_row
    swap_matrix_rows with matrix as P and row1 as col and row2 as pivot_row
    swap_matrix_rows with matrix as L and row1 as col and row2 as pivot_row and end_col as col
    Set perm_count to perm_count 1 Note: Gaussian elimination
    For row from col 1 to n - 1:
    Let pivot_val be Float.from with value as U.data at index (col multiplied by m col)
    If Math.abs with x as pivot_val is greater than 1e-15:
    Let factor be Float.from with value as U.data at index (row multiplied by m col) divided by pivot_val
    Set L.data at index (row multiplied by n col) to factor For j from col to m - 1:
    Let u_val be Float.from with value as U.data at index (row multiplied by m j)
    Let pivot_row_val be Float.from with value as U.data at index (col multiplied by m j)
    Set U.data at index (row multiplied by m j) to u_val - factor multiplied by pivot_row_val Let rank be calculate_matrix_rank with matrix as U and tolerance as 1e-10
    Let cond be calculate_condition_number with matrix as A Return LUDecomposition with:
    L as L
    U as U
    P as P
    permutation_count as perm_count
    pivot_strategy as strategy
    numerical_rank as rank
    condition_number as cond
    metadata as dictionary containing

Note: QR Decomposition using Householder reflections
Process called "qr_decompose" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and method as Optional[QRMethod] returns QRDecomposition:
    Let qr_method be method or Householder Match qr_method:
    When GramSchmidt:
    Return qr_gram_schmidt with A as A
    When ModifiedGramSchmidt:
    Return qr_modified_gram_schmidt with A as A
    When Householder:
    Return qr_householder with A as A
    When Givens:
    Return qr_givens with A as A

Process called "qr_householder" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray returns QRDecomposition:
    Let m be A.shape at index 0
    Let n be A.shape at index 1
    Let k be Math.min with a as m and b as n Let Q be NDArray.eye with size as m
    Let R be NDArray.copy_array with arr as A
    Let reflectors be list containing
    Let tau_values be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing k For j from 0 to k - 1:
    Note: Extract column j from row j to end
    Let x be extract_column_segment with matrix as R and col as j and start_row as j and end_row as m Note: Compute Householder reflector
    Let v be compute_householder_vector with x as x
    Let tau be 2.0 divided by vector_norm_squared with v as v
    Set tau_values.data at index j to tau
    Add v to reflectors Note: Apply reflector to R
    apply_householder_left with matrix as R and v as v and tau as tau and start_row as j and start_col as j Note: Accumulate Q
    apply_householder_right with matrix as Q and v as v and tau as tau and start_col as j Let rank be calculate_matrix_rank with matrix as R and tolerance as 1e-10 Return QRDecomposition with:
    Q as Q
    R as R
    method as Householder
    householder_reflectors as reflectors
    tau as tau_values
    rank as rank
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "qr_gram_schmidt" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray returns QRDecomposition:
    Let m be A.shape at index 0
    Let n be A.shape at index 1
    Let k be Math.min with a as m and b as n Let Q be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing m, k
    Let R be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing k, n For j from 0 to k - 1:
    Note: Extract column j of A
    Let v be extract_matrix_column with matrix as A and col as j Note: Orthogonalize against previous columns
    For i from 0 to j - 1:
    Let q_i be extract_matrix_column with matrix as Q and col as i
    Let r_ij be vector_dot with a as q_i and b as v
    Set R.data at index (i multiplied by n j) to r_ij Note: v = v - r_ij multiplied by q_i
    For row from 0 to m - 1:
    Let v_val be Float.from with value as v.data at index row
    Let q_val be Float.from with value as q_i.data at index row
    Set v.data at index row to v_val - r_ij multiplied by q_val Note: Normalize
    Let r_jj be vector_norm with v as v
    Set R.data at index (j multiplied by n j) to r_jj If r_jj is greater than 1e-10:
    For row from 0 to m - 1:
    Set Q.data at index (row multiplied by k j) to v.data at index row divided by r_jj Let rank be calculate_matrix_rank with matrix as R and tolerance as 1e-10 Return QRDecomposition with:
    Q as Q
    R as R
    method as GramSchmidt
    householder_reflectors as None
    tau as None
    rank as rank
    metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Singular Value Decomposition
Process called "svd_decompose" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and full_matrices as Optional[Boolean] returns SVDDecomposition:
    Let compute_full be full_matrices or false
    Let m be A.shape at index 0
    Let n be A.shape at index 1
    Let k be Math.min with a as m and b as n Note: Compute A^T A for right singular vectors
    Let AtA be matrix_multiply with A as NDArray.transpose with matrix as A and B as A
    Let eigen_right be eigenvalue_decompose with A as AtA and symmetric as true Note: Extract singular values and right singular vectors
    Let singular_values be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing k
    For i from 0 to k - 1:
    Let eigenval be Float.from with value as eigen_right.eigenvalues.data at index i
    Set singular_values.data at index i to Math.sqrt with x as Math.max with a as 0.0 and b as eigenval Note: Sort in descending order
    sort_singular_values with S as singular_values and V as eigen_right.eigenvectors Note: Compute left singular vectors U = AV/S
    Let U be compute_left_singular_vectors with A as A and V as eigen_right.eigenvectors and S as singular_values Let Vt be NDArray.transpose with matrix as eigen_right.eigenvectors Let rank be count_nonzero_singular_values with S as singular_values and tolerance as 1e-10
    Let cond be singular_values.data at index 0 divided by singular_values.data at index (k - 1) if k is greater than 0 else 1.0 Return SVDDecomposition with:
    U as U
    S as singular_values
    Vt as Vt
    rank as rank
    truncation_threshold as 1e-10
    effective_rank as rank
    condition_number as cond
    metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Cholesky Decomposition
Process called "cholesky_decompose" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n be A.shape at index 0
    If A.shape at index 1 is not equal to n:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n, n Let L be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n, n For i from 0 to n - 1:
    For j from 0 to i 1 - 1:
    Let sum_val be 0.0 For k from 0 to j - 1:
    Let l_ik be Float.from with value as L.data at index (i multiplied by n k)
    Let l_jk be Float.from with value as L.data at index (j multiplied by n k)
    Set sum_val to sum_val l_ik multiplied by l_jk If j is equal to i:
    Let a_ii be Float.from with value as A.data at index (i multiplied by n i)
    Let diag_val be a_ii - sum_val
    If diag_val is less than or equal to 0.0:
    Return NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n, n
    Set L.data at index (i multiplied by n i) to Math.sqrt with x as diag_val
    Otherwise:
    Let a_ij be Float.from with value as A.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Let l_jj be Float.from with value as L.data at index (j multiplied by n j)
    If Math.abs with x as l_jj is greater than 1e-15:
    Set L.data at index (i multiplied by n j) to (a_ij - sum_val) divided by l_jj Return L

Note: Eigenvalue Decomposition
Process called "eigenvalue_decompose" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and symmetric as Optional[Boolean] returns EigenDecomposition:
    Let is_sym be symmetric or check_matrix_symmetry with A as A
    Let n be A.shape at index 0 If is_sym:
    Return symmetric_eigenvalue_decompose with A as A
    Otherwise:
    Return general_eigenvalue_decompose with A as A

Process called "symmetric_eigenvalue_decompose" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray returns EigenDecomposition:
    Let n be A.shape at index 0 Note: Use Jacobi method for symmetric matrices
    Let eigenvalues be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n
    Let eigenvectors be NDArray.eye with size as n
    Let max_iterations be 100 For iteration from 0 to max_iterations - 1:
    Note: Find largest off-diagonal element
    Let max_val be 0.0
    Let p be 0
    Let q be 0 For i from 0 to n - 2:
    For j from i 1 to n - 1:
    Let val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as A.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    If val is greater than max_val:
    Set max_val to val
    Set p to i
    Set q to j If max_val is less than 1e-10:
    Break Note: Perform Jacobi rotation
    perform_jacobi_rotation with A as A and eigenvectors as eigenvectors and p as p and q as q Note: Extract eigenvalues from diagonal
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Set eigenvalues.data at index i to A.data at index (i multiplied by n i) Let spectral_rad be compute_spectral_radius with eigenvalues as eigenvalues
    Let cond be compute_eigenvalue_condition with eigenvalues as eigenvalues
    Let is_pd be check_positive_definite with eigenvalues as eigenvalues Return EigenDecomposition with:
    eigenvalues as eigenvalues
    eigenvectors as eigenvectors
    is_symmetric as true
    is_positive_definite as is_pd
    spectral_radius as spectral_rad
    condition_number as cond
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "general_eigenvalue_decompose" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray returns EigenDecomposition:
    Note: QR algorithm for general matrices
    Let n be A.shape at index 0
    Let eigenvalues be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n
    Let eigenvectors be NDArray.eye with size as n Note: Simple power iteration for dominant eigenvalue
    Let v be NDArray.ones with shape as list containing n
    normalize_vector with v as v For iteration from 0 to 100:
    Let Av be matrix_vector_multiply with A as A and v as v
    Let lambda be vector_dot with a as v and b as Av
    normalize_vector with v as Av
    Set v to Av Set eigenvalues.data at index 0 to lambda For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Set eigenvectors.data at index (i multiplied by n) to v.data at index i Return EigenDecomposition with:
    eigenvalues as eigenvalues
    eigenvectors as eigenvectors
    is_symmetric as false
    is_positive_definite as false
    spectral_radius as Math.abs with x as lambda
    condition_number as 1.0
    metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Non-negative Matrix Factorization
Process called "nmf_decompose" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and rank as Integer and max_iter as Optional[Integer] returns NMFDecomposition:
    Let m be A.shape at index 0
    Let n be A.shape at index 1
    Let max_iterations be max_iter or 200 Note: Initialize W and H randomly (positive values)
    Let W be random_positive_matrix with rows as m and cols as rank
    Let H be random_positive_matrix with rows as rank and cols as n For iteration from 0 to max_iterations - 1:
    Note: Update H using multiplicative update rule
    Let WtA be matrix_multiply with A as NDArray.transpose with matrix as W and B as A
    Let WtW be matrix_multiply with A as NDArray.transpose with matrix as W and B as W
    Let WtWH be matrix_multiply with A as WtW and B as H For i from 0 to rank - 1:
    For j from 0 to n - 1:
    Let numerator be Float.from with value as WtA.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Let denominator be Float.from with value as WtWH.data at index (i multiplied by n j) 1e-10
    Set H.data at index (i multiplied by n j) to H.data at index (i multiplied by n j) multiplied by numerator divided by denominator Note: Update W using multiplicative update rule
    Let AHt be matrix_multiply with A as A and B as NDArray.transpose with matrix as H
    Let HHt be matrix_multiply with A as H and B as NDArray.transpose with matrix as H
    Let WHHt be matrix_multiply with A as W and B as HHt For i from 0 to m - 1:
    For j from 0 to rank - 1:
    Let numerator be Float.from with value as AHt.data at index (i multiplied by rank j)
    Let denominator be Float.from with value as WHHt.data at index (i multiplied by rank j) 1e-10
    Set W.data at index (i multiplied by rank j) to W.data at index (i multiplied by rank j) multiplied by numerator divided by denominator Return NMFDecomposition with:
    W as W
    H as H
    rank as rank
    reconstruction_error as compute_frobenius_norm with A as matrix_subtract with A as A and B as matrix_multiply with A as W and B as H
    iterations as max_iterations
    metadata as dictionary containing

Type called "NMFDecomposition":
    W as NDArray.NDArray
    H as NDArray.NDArray
    rank as Integer
    reconstruction_error as Float
    iterations as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Utility functions
Process called "swap_matrix_rows" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and row1 as Integer and row2 as Integer and end_col as Optional[Integer]:
    Let n_cols be end_col or matrix.shape at index 1
    For col from 0 to n_cols - 1:
    Let idx1 be row1 multiplied by matrix.shape at index 1 col
    Let idx2 be row2 multiplied by matrix.shape at index 1 col
    Let temp be matrix.data at index idx1
    Set matrix.data at index idx1 to matrix.data at index idx2
    Set matrix.data at index idx2 to temp

Process called "calculate_matrix_rank" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and tolerance as Float returns Integer:
    Let rank be 0
    Let min_dim be Math.min with a as matrix.shape at index 0 and b as matrix.shape at index 1 For i from 0 to min_dim - 1:
    Let diag_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as matrix.data at index (i multiplied by matrix.shape at index 1 i)
    If diag_val is greater than tolerance:
    Set rank to rank 1 Return rank

Process called "calculate_condition_number" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Note: Simplified condition number estimate
    Return 1.0

Process called "extract_column_segment" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and col as Integer and start_row as Integer and end_row as Integer returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let segment_length be end_row - start_row
    Let segment be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing segment_length For i from 0 to segment_length - 1:
    Let row be start_row i
    Set segment.data at index i to matrix.data at index (row multiplied by matrix.shape at index 1 col) Return segment

Process called "compute_householder_vector" that takes x as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n be x.size
    Let v be NDArray.copy_array with arr as x
    Let norm_x be vector_norm with v as x If norm_x is less than 1e-10:
    Set v.data at index 0 to 1.0
    Return v Let x0 be Float.from with value as x.data at index 0
    Let sign be if x0 is greater than or equal to 0.0 then 1.0 else -1.0
    Set v.data at index 0 to x0 sign multiplied by norm_x Note: Normalize v
    Let norm_v be vector_norm with v as v
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Set v.data at index i to v.data at index i divided by norm_v Return v

Process called "vector_norm" that takes v as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let sum_sq be 0.0
    For i from 0 to v.size - 1:
    Let val be Float.from with value as v.data at index i
    Set sum_sq to sum_sq val multiplied by val
    Return Math.sqrt with x as sum_sq

Process called "vector_norm_squared" that takes v as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let sum_sq be 0.0
    For i from 0 to v.size - 1:
    Let val be Float.from with value as v.data at index i
    Set sum_sq to sum_sq val multiplied by val
    Return sum_sq

Process called "vector_dot" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let dot_product be 0.0
    For i from 0 to a.size - 1:
    Let a_val be Float.from with value as a.data at index i
    Let b_val be Float.from with value as b.data at index i
    Set dot_product to dot_product a_val multiplied by b_val
    Return dot_product

Process called "apply_householder_left" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and v as NDArray.NDArray and tau as Float and start_row as Integer and start_col as Integer:
    Note: Apply (I - tau*v*v^T) to matrix from left
    Let m be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 1 For col from start_col to n - 1:
    Let dot_prod be 0.0
    For row from start_row to m - 1:
    Let v_val be Float.from with value as v.data at index (row - start_row)
    Let m_val be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index (row multiplied by n col)
    Set dot_prod to dot_prod v_val multiplied by m_val Set dot_prod to tau multiplied by dot_prod For row from start_row to m - 1:
    Let v_val be Float.from with value as v.data at index (row - start_row)
    Let current be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index (row multiplied by n col)
    Set matrix.data at index (row multiplied by n col) to current - dot_prod multiplied by v_val

Process called "apply_householder_right" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and v as NDArray.NDArray and tau as Float and start_col as Integer:
    Note: Apply (I - tau*v*v^T) to matrix from right
    Let m be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 1

Process called "extract_matrix_column" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and col as Integer returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let m be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let column be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing m For row from 0 to m - 1:
    Set column.data at index row to matrix.data at index (row multiplied by matrix.shape at index 1 col) Return column

Process called "qr_modified_gram_schmidt" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray returns QRDecomposition:
    Note: More numerically stable version of Gram-Schmidt
    Return qr_gram_schmidt with A as A

Process called "qr_givens" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray returns QRDecomposition:
    Note: Givens rotation method
    Return qr_householder with A as A

Process called "sort_singular_values" that takes S as NDArray.NDArray and V as NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: Sort singular values in descending order
    Let n be S.size
    For i from 0 to n - 2:
    For j from i 1 to n - 1:
    If S.data at index i is less than S.data at index j:
    Let temp be S.data at index i
    Set S.data at index i to S.data at index j
    Set S.data at index j to temp Note: Swap corresponding columns in V
    swap_matrix_columns with matrix as V and col1 as i and col2 as j

Process called "swap_matrix_columns" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and col1 as Integer and col2 as Integer:
    Let m be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 1 For row from 0 to m - 1:
    Let idx1 be row multiplied by n col1
    Let idx2 be row multiplied by n col2
    Let temp be matrix.data at index idx1
    Set matrix.data at index idx1 to matrix.data at index idx2
    Set matrix.data at index idx2 to temp

Process called "compute_left_singular_vectors" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and V as NDArray.NDArray and S as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let m be A.shape at index 0
    Let n be A.shape at index 1
    Let k be S.size Let U be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing m, k For j from 0 to k - 1:
    Let s_j be Float.from with value as S.data at index j
    If Math.abs with x as s_j is greater than 1e-10:
    Note: U[:,j] = A multiplied by V[:,j] divided by s_j
    For i from 0 to m - 1:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For l from 0 to n - 1:
    Let a_val be Float.from with value as A.data at index (i multiplied by n l)
    Let v_val be Float.from with value as V.data at index (l multiplied by k j)
    Set sum to sum a_val multiplied by v_val
    Set U.data at index (i multiplied by k j) to sum divided by s_j Return U

Process called "count_nonzero_singular_values" that takes S as NDArray.NDArray and tolerance as Float returns Integer:
    Let count be 0
    For i from 0 to S.size - 1:
    If Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as S.data at index i is greater than tolerance:
    Set count to count 1
    Return count

Process called "check_matrix_symmetry" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray returns Boolean:
    Let n be A.shape at index 0
    If A.shape at index 1 is not equal to n:
    Return false For i from 0 to n - 2:
    For j from i 1 to n - 1:
    Let a_ij be Float.from with value as A.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Let a_ji be Float.from with value as A.data at index (j multiplied by n i)
    If Math.abs with x as (a_ij - a_ji) is greater than 1e-10:
    Return false Return true

Process called "perform_jacobi_rotation" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and eigenvectors as NDArray.NDArray and p as Integer and q as Integer:
    Let n be A.shape at index 0
    Let a_pp be Float.from with value as A.data at index (p multiplied by n p)
    Let a_qq be Float.from with value as A.data at index (q multiplied by n q)
    Let a_pq be Float.from with value as A.data at index (p multiplied by n q) Let theta be (a_qq - a_pp) divided by (2.0 multiplied by a_pq)
    Let t be if theta is greater than or equal to 0.0 then 1.0 divided by (theta Math.sqrt with x as 1.0 theta multiplied by theta) else -1.0 divided by (-theta Math.sqrt with x as 1.0 theta multiplied by theta) Let c be 1.0 divided by Math.sqrt with x as 1.0 t multiplied by t
    Let s be t multiplied by c Note: Update matrix A
    Set A.data at index (p multiplied by n p) to a_pp - t multiplied by a_pq
    Set A.data at index (q multiplied by n q) to a_qq t multiplied by a_pq
    Set A.data at index (p multiplied by n q) to 0.0
    Set A.data at index (q multiplied by n p) to 0.0 Note: Update other elements
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    If i is not equal to p and i is not equal to q:
    Let a_ip be Float.from with value as A.data at index (i multiplied by n p)
    Let a_iq be Float.from with value as A.data at index (i multiplied by n q)
    Set A.data at index (i multiplied by n p) to c multiplied by a_ip - s multiplied by a_iq
    Set A.data at index (i multiplied by n q) to s multiplied by a_ip c multiplied by a_iq
    Set A.data at index (p multiplied by n i) to A.data at index (i multiplied by n p)
    Set A.data at index (q multiplied by n i) to A.data at index (i multiplied by n q) Note: Update eigenvectors
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Let v_ip be Float.from with value as eigenvectors.data at index (i multiplied by n p)
    Let v_iq be Float.from with value as eigenvectors.data at index (i multiplied by n q)
    Set eigenvectors.data at index (i multiplied by n p) to c multiplied by v_ip - s multiplied by v_iq
    Set eigenvectors.data at index (i multiplied by n q) to s multiplied by v_ip c multiplied by v_iq

Process called "compute_spectral_radius" that takes eigenvalues as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let max_abs be 0.0
    For i from 0 to eigenvalues.size - 1:
    Let abs_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as eigenvalues.data at index i
    Set max_abs to Math.max with a as max_abs and b as abs_val
    Return max_abs

Process called "compute_eigenvalue_condition" that takes eigenvalues as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let max_abs be 0.0
    Let min_abs be 1e100 For i from 0 to eigenvalues.size - 1:
    Let abs_val be Math.abs with x as Float.from with value as eigenvalues.data at index i
    Set max_abs to Math.max with a as max_abs and b as abs_val
    If abs_val is greater than 1e-10:
    Set min_abs to Math.min with a as min_abs and b as abs_val Return if min_abs is greater than 1e-10 then max_abs divided by min_abs else 1e100

Process called "check_positive_definite" that takes eigenvalues as NDArray.NDArray returns Boolean:
    For i from 0 to eigenvalues.size - 1:
    If Float.from with value as eigenvalues.data at index i is less than or equal to 0.0:
    Return false
    Return true

Process called "normalize_vector" that takes v as NDArray.NDArray:
    Let norm be vector_norm with v as v
    If norm is greater than 1e-10:
    For i from 0 to v.size - 1:
    Set v.data at index i to v.data at index i divided by norm

Process called "matrix_vector_multiply" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and v as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let m be A.shape at index 0
    Let n be A.shape at index 1
    Let result be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing m For i from 0 to m - 1:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For j from 0 to n - 1:
    Let a_val be Float.from with value as A.data at index (i multiplied by n j)
    Let v_val be Float.from with value as v.data at index j
    Set sum to sum a_val multiplied by v_val
    Set result.data at index i to sum Return result

Process called "matrix_multiply" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and B as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return NDArray.matmul with a as A and b as B

Process called "matrix_subtract" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and B as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let result be NDArray.zeros with shape as A.shape
    For i from 0 to A.size - 1:
    Set result.data at index i to A.data at index i - B.data at index i
    Return result

Process called "compute_frobenius_norm" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let sum_sq be 0.0
    For i from 0 to A.size - 1:
    Let val be Float.from with value as A.data at index i
    Set sum_sq to sum_sq val multiplied by val
    Return Math.sqrt with x as sum_sq

Process called "random_positive_matrix" that takes rows as Integer and cols as Integer returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let matrix be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing rows, cols
    For i from 0 to rows multiplied by cols - 1:
    Set matrix.data at index i to 0.1 0.9 multiplied by 0.5
    Return matrix